'''Vickon Greyjoy''' is an unseen character in ''[[Game of Thrones (TV series)|Game of Thrones]]''. He is deceased when the events of the series begin.

Lord Vickon was the head of [[House Greyjoy]] and the [[Lord Reaper of Pyke]] during the reign of King [[Harren Hoare|Harren the Black]] of [[House Hoare]]. After Harren and his line were burned alive by [[Aegon I Targaryen|Aegon the Conqueror]] inside his castle of [[Harrenhal]], the [[ironborn]] were expelled from [[the Riverlands]] back to the [[Iron Islands]]. In exchange for their allegiance, Aegon allowed theÂ ironborn to choose their new leader. They chose Vickon Greyjoy: his House was one of the most prominent in the Isles, claiming descent from the legendary [[Grey King]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[House Greyjoy (Histories &amp; Lore)]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
